import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['region', 'income']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['region'] == 'northeast']['income'], 
                data[data['region'] == 'midwest']['income'], 
                data[data['region'] == 'south']['income']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Northeast', 'Midwest', 'South'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Income')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    plt.ylabel('Income')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income and percentage of population in a region?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['income'], bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='income')
    plt.xlabel('Income')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('Histogram of income by income group')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by=['region'])
    regions = data['region'].unique()
    pct = data.groupby(['region'])['pct'].sum().values
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(regions, pct, color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Percentage of Population')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of percentage of population across different regions?')
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
